{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, Jia, Chen [77] presented a DL and bioinformatics-based approach for the identification of breast cancer cases.",
    "The authors used a dataset consisting of 212 breast cancer patients and 212 healthy controls.",
    "The transcriptome data of these samples were analyzed using bioinformatics tools to identify Differentially Expressed Genes (DEGs).",
    "The DEGs were then used as input for a DL algorithm, which was trained to classify the samples as cancerous or non-cancerous.",
    "The authors reported high accuracy and specificity in the classification of the samples using this approach."
  ]
}